  "name": "Shadow Snare",
  "type": "spell",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Access</strong> leather wing</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Cast </strong>[two-actions] somatic, verbal</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Range </strong>30 feet; <strong>Targets</strong> 1 creatures</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Duration </strong>1 minute</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Save </strong>Reflex</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Ensnaring a foe with sudden tendrils of semi-real shadow, the victim gains the immobilized condition. A creature so affected can free itself with [two-actions] or be freed by an adjacent ally that spends [two-actions] providing aid. Shadow snare is not tethered to any other object. Once caught in a shadow snare, a person cannot be snared again by you until the next time you do your daily preparations.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Critical Success </strong>The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Success </strong>The spell's duration is only 1 round.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Failure The spell works normally.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Critical Failure Removing the snare requires [three-actions].</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>"
